        "problem": {
            "headline": "Our drivers deliver 14/day while the competitor's app does 22",
            "description": "FreshFleet is a 12-driver delivery co-op serving a mid-size city. Orders come in by phone, dispatching is done on a whiteboard, drivers navigate with paper route sheets, and customers call asking \"where's my package?\" A larger competitor with a slick app is eating our market share. We're losing 2-3 regular accounts per month. Drivers spend 35% of their day on wasted miles — returning to depot, backtracking, sitting in avoidable traffic. The dispatcher spends more time answering \"where is it?\" calls than actually dispatching. Paper manifests have caused 3-4 lost packages per month ($2K/month in claims). Customers wait at home all day because we can't give them a delivery window.",
            "impactMetric": {
                "kpiId": "deliveries_per_driver",
                "value": 14,
                "unit": "deliveries/driver/day"
            },
            "evidence": [
                { "label": "Driver ride-along time study (Jan 2026)", "url": "driver-ridealong-time-study-jan2026.pdf", "addedAt": "2026-01-18T10:00:00Z", "addedBy": "ops@freshfleet.coop" },
